		<p style="color: #919191;"><i>July 30th, 2014</i></p><br><br>
		<p class="big">
		Last weekend, I was flipping through Southwest’s Spirit Magazine while on a short flight from LAX to SFO. I read about a woman named Nicole Kear, and <a href="http://www.spiritmag.com/features/article/as_the_lights_go_down/">her slow descent into blindness</a>. At age 19, she had received a diagnosis of an incurable retinal disease, and was told by the specialist that she would be completely blind by age 40.
		</p>
