<div class="text-block row">
	<div class="large-8 columns large-offset-2">
		<p class="big">

		A tool is something that amplifies human capability so it can meet a defined need. I think of VSCO as an amazing example of this. With your tools, we can take what we see, imbue it with our individual mood and meaning, and make it instantly communicable with someone else – all without words. VSCO is a way through which we can extend our natural human powers.
		</p>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="divider"></div>

<div class="text-block row">
	<div class="large-8 columns large-offset-2">
		<p class="big">
		Right now, many startups in the Bay Area aren’t creating tools – they’re creating services. I can now hire someone to clean my house, do my dry cleaning, drive me somewhere – basically, these companies are helping me to <i>not</i> do certain things.
		<br><br>To me, VSCO does the opposite. It encourages us to get out of our offices, to move, to explore the world, appreciate the details and the little moments – to not be blind to the beauty around us.
		</p>
	</div>
</div>

